Module Name:
Model Evaluation

Objective:
To evaluate the performance of the trained Logistic Regression model.

Evaluation Metrics Used:
1. Accuracy Score
2. Confusion Matrix
3. Classification Report

Description:
Model evaluation is performed to measure how accurately the trained model predicts crop recommendations.

Accuracy Score:
Measures the percentage of correct predictions made by the model.

Confusion Matrix:
Displays actual and predicted classifications for performance analysis.

Classification Report:
Provides precision, recall, F1-score, and support values for each crop class.

Tools Used:
• Python
• Scikit-Learn
• Pandas
• Jupyter Notebook

Output:
• Accuracy Score
• Confusion Matrix
• Classification Report

Conclusion:
The Logistic Regression model is evaluated using standard classification metrics to determine its prediction performance and reliability.
